    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-27T11:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-27T11:50:00-05:00" n="811"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.21112A/9–2744: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-27T11:50:00-05:00"
                            >September 27, 1944—11:50 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 11—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–851. The local press reports that the first resolutions covering expropriation
                    of certain spearhead Nazi firms in Colombia have been issued by Ministry of
                    Finance and sent to Attorney General for immediate action. The corresponding
                    suits will be instituted by Attorney General before the National Judge of Prices
                    (Juez Nacional de Precios) in accordance with Executive Decree 1723 of July 25,
                    1944 establishing the routine procedure in such cases. Because of very <pb
                        facs="0864" n="850" xml:id="pg_850"/> detailed nature of proceedings,
                    progress of suits will likely be somewhat slow.</p>
                <p>Minister of Government informed me Tuesday morning that La Química Bayer–Weskott
                    &amp; Cía. and Química Schering Colombiana were included in resolutions already
                    issued.</p>
                <p>Officers of the Embassy were also informed by officials of the Stabilization Fund
                    on Wednesday that the first resolutions included also Empresa Hanseática,
                    Instituto Behring, Anilinas Alemanas, and Cía. Colombiana de Colorantes y
                    Productos Químicos, Ltda., and that additional resolutions covering other German
                    firms would be issued within the near future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
